description: McElhenney says he bought the team to “bring hope to a town that had fallen on hard times." The FX series Welcome to Wrexham chronicles the team and its owners and fans.
title: 'Always Sunny' creator Rob McElhenney on his pandemic purchase: a Welsh soccer team

description: The 16-time reigning champion lost his spot in this year's competition after signing an endorsement deal with a company that makes plant-based hot dogs, potentially clearing the way for an underdog.
title: Hot dog-eating champ Joey Chestnut won't compete this July 4. What’s the beef?

description: A new documentary by the hip-hop historian and critic dream hampton, culled from her own never-before-seen footage of rap's golden age, illustrates the hard labor for women who love the music.
title: ‘It Was All a Dream’ shows the work of a nascent rap feminist

description: Paul Tremblay's latest tale is dark, surprisingly violent, and incredibly multilayered — a superb addition to his already impressive oeuvre showing he can deliver for fans and also push the envelope.
title: 'Horror Movie' questions the motivation behind evil acts

description: Listeners explain why they decided to remain friends with their exes, keep a friendly distance — or leave them behind.
title: When a romance ends, can a friendship grow? NPR listeners weigh in

description: The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau released proposed federal regulations that would prevent unpaid medical bills from being counted on consumers’ credit reports.
title: Biden administration announces a plan for removing medical debt from credit reports

description: For a seventh straight week, Taylor Swift’s The Tortured Poets Department rules the Billboard 200. On the singles chart, Eminem references both the Steve Miller Band and his own past glory.
title: The top songs of the week take a nostalgia trip, courtesy of Eminem

description: The Seinfeld star plays the mother of a terminally ill girl being visited by Death, who has taken the physical form of a giant parrot, in new film.
title: Julia Louis-Dreyfus goes from 'Veep' to weep in new tearjerker film 'Tuesday'

description: Hawaii's unique birds, known as honeycreepers, are being wiped out by mosquitoes carrying avian malaria. The birds' last hope could be more mosquitoes, designed to crash their own population.
title: Hawaii's birds are going extinct. Their last hope could be millions of mosquitoes
